text: Nassarius cockburnensis is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae, the Nassa mud snails or dog whelks. ==Description== The length of the shell varies between 6.9 mm and 9.7 mm. ==Distribution== This marine species occurs off Western Australia. ==References== * Kool H.H. & Dekker H. (2006) Review of the Nassarius pauper (Gould, 1850) complex (Gastropoda: Nassariidae). Part 1, with the description of four new species from the Indo-West Pacific. Visaya 1(6): 54–75. page(s): 57 Category:Nassariidae Category:Gastropods described in 2006
title: Nassarius cockburnensis
